Excellent coffee here and good food too!
Underrated cafe. The barista knows his beans enough to make a non-acidic batch brew which warms me up on a breezy mid morning. Don't take my words for it: try it out for yourself.

result.name: Coffee Roastery Lab Sheung Wan

reviews.text:
- Good place to work! I drop by during lunch time but it is not crowded, which is good!
- Coffee Roastery Lab belongs to 18Grams.
- Outdoor seating available!

Very quiet coffee shop... They have awesome coffee at very reasonable price, great service and ample seating available and wifi

Since it's tucked inside the small street... Doesn't attract much crowd...

Coffee and food are decently priced, a rarity for Central. Four stars for having wifi (though not very fast) and ample space to work, also a rarity in Hong Kong. The shop is hard to find which is probably the only reason why there's room to work on your laptop. Staff are great, attentive and friendly.

Very good coffee and quick service, but cannot recommend the ‘Benedict’ meals. The ingredients themselves seemed to be decent in quality and freshness. Unfortunately though, they were pre-prepared and, except for some lukewarm toast, served without being reheated. First time I’ve eaten room temperature soft poached egg and I’m not in a hurry to repeat the experience!
Really great banana bread and pretty decent coffee. Place has nice decor.
